    "transliteration":
    """The author of 'Kasasul Ambiya' writes that his father has written that he had seen the writings of Janabe Aakhund Mulla Mohammed Baqar (a.s.) that this humble servant of Allah (s.w.t.) was looking at Duas on a Friday night. He saw one dua which was small but it touched the heart. So he recited, that dua. Next Friday night I felt like reciting that dua again. Suddenly, a voice came from the roof, 'O Ayyohal Fazelul Qamil, 'Keramin Katebeen are still writing the sawab (reward) of the dua which you recited last Friday. You want to recite this dua second time' It is this dua:

